------------------------------------
eksctl and existing VPC:
ЁЯФ╣ Production рдордзреНрдпреЗ рдХрд╕рдВ рдХрд░рддрд╛рдд?

Production setup рд╕рд╛рдареА default VPC рд╡рд╛рдкрд░рдгрдВ recommend рдирд╛рд╣реА.
рддреНрдпрд╛рдРрд╡рдЬреА:

Custom VPC рддрдпрд╛рд░ рдХрд░рддрд╛рдд (Terraform, CloudFormation рдХрд┐рдВрд╡рд╛ manually).

рддреНрдпрд╛ VPC рдордзреНрдпреЗ subnets define рдХрд░рддрд╛рдд:

Private subnets тЖТ worker nodes, pods (secure workloads).

Public subnets тЖТ Load balancers, NAT gateways.

рдирдВрддрд░ eksctl рдХрд┐рдВрд╡рд╛ Terraform рд╡рд╛рдкрд░реВрди cluster рддрдпрд╛рд░ рдХрд░рддрд╛рдирд╛ рддреНрдпрд╛ existing VPC + subnets specify рдХрд░рддрд╛рдд.
------------------------------
ЁЯФ╣ Why Custom VPC in Production?

Networking control (CIDR ranges, peering, security).

Multi-AZ HA design (subnets spread across AZs).

On-prem connectivity (VPN/Direct Connect).

Compliance & security policies (private-only workloads).

Reusability (multiple clusters in same VPC).
----------------
Example with eksctl and existing VPC
eksctl create cluster -f cluster.yaml
--------------------------------------
Web Tier:     10 replicas  (high, to handle many concurrent users)
App Tier:     8 replicas   (slightly less than web tier)
Database:     3 replicas   (1 primary + 2 read replicas)
-----------------------------

